The sensitivity of the system regarding the number of nucleotide copies was evaluated by using known amounts of recombinant viral RNA obtained from the Lelystad, the Soz-8, and the Ingelvac MLV® strain. The detection limit was ten copies of viral RNA in the reaction mixture and the assay allowed linear detection in the range of 100–1010 RNA copies/reaction. The standard curves were obtained with the Lelystad and the Ingelvac MLV® strain. All reactions were performed in triplicate, and the mean data of cycle threshold was used to design the standard curves (Fig. 2
). The PCR efficiency (E) was 0.99 in case of the Lelystad virus, and 1.00 in case of the the Ingelvac MLV® strain, whereas the correlation efficient (R
2) was 0.99 in both cases.
